<title type="html"><![CDATA[Skull &amp; Crossbones - Split Screen Shakes - Nestopia]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11525&amp;p=132453#p132453"><![CDATA[
Under Nestopia (Undead) 1.45 (and older versions), as well as the (un)official releases (I.E. 1.40-1.42), when you split the screen by starting the second player in Skull &amp; Crossbones in-game, the bottom portion shakes and there's some graphic corruption.<br /><br />The ROM dump, per Nestopia's launcher shows it as a &quot;Good&quot; dump.  Presuming then, it's an emulation issue (?)  <br /><br />Trying Nintendulator (Aug 10, 2014 beta), there's some minor graphic corruption (Just below 2nd player/&quot;RED DOG&quot; status info), but no shaking screen with the 2nd players enabled utilizing the same ROM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=250">trebor</a> — Tue Aug 12, 2014 11:20 am</p><hr />
